data.event: Many Cherokee families settled in Ina around 1840.
Spring Garden prospered from 1848 until the Chicago and Eastern Illinois Railroad was built in 1905.

A famous double murder occurred in Ina in 1924, when Rev. Lawrence Hight and his lover Elsie Sweeten poisoned Sweeten's husband, in July, and Hight's wife in September.
